{
  "text": "Dutch patients usually register at a single pharmacy, and therefore an almost complete overview of drug history, excluding over-the-counter medications and in-hospital prescriptions, can be achieved. The database records longitudinal drug prescriptions records from more than 50 community pharmacies in The Netherlands, covering a population of 500 000 people since 1999. The number of children aged 0-18 years in this population was approximately 123 000 in 2008 [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "21597290",
    "[CITATION_2]": "37274541"
